    <Text name="Improvements to mirror reality better" LabelPosition="Middle" Note="&lt;ol&gt;&lt;li&gt;​Symptomatic Infected people would have a lower # of contacts &lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Divide people into Asymptomatic Infected and Symptomatic Infected since Asymptomatic infected can still be around and about infecting others while Symptomatic Infected would be sequestered to bed. and both groups would have different # of contacts / day&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Fraction of People wo immunity is to small of a fraction to give rise to system level impacts. More interesting to simulate people becoming susceptible after 180-200 days again.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ol&gt;" id="64">
      <mxCell style="text;fontSize=18;fontFamily=Verdana;" parent="1" vertex="1">
        <mxGeometry x="30" y="588" width="370" height="65" as="geometry" />
      </mxCell>
    </Text>
    <Text name="Simulation - README" LabelPosition="Middle" Note="This simulation will allow you to experiment with various parameters ​for the COVID-19 Virus.&amp;nbsp; Remember that SEIR Models are good to experiment with various epidemological factors and how they change the dynamics and possible pathways but might not mirror reality in all cases.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;ol&gt;&lt;li&gt;Vaccines will be available from day 10 onwards. You can change what the max rate for vaccinations will be but it will take approx 20 days from start of vaccinations until we get close to the max vaccination rate.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;First test changing the following variables to see what happens:&lt;br&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Incubation Period&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Days Infected&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Contacts Per Day&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Infectivity&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ol&gt;" id="65">
      <mxCell style="text;fontFamily=Verdana;fontSize=18;" parent="1" vertex="1">
        <mxGeometry x="60" y="520" width="300" height="70" as="geometry" />
      </mxCell>
    </Text>
